{
  "texts": [
    "We define the handedness of the parallelogram as CW for δ ∈ (0, 0.5) and CCW for δ ∈ (0.5, 1) (Fig. 9c, d).",
    "D eff (δ) for CAPs are qualitatively similar at different r values (Fig. S12).",
    "Figure 9f shows that D eff for CW and CCW particles are mirror-symmetric about δ = 0.5 because lattices with the same |δ -0.5| are mirror images with the same magnitude of chirality.",
    "Thus, Fig. 9g only shows ΔD eff = D CW -D CCW ∈ [0, 0.5].",
    "ΔD eff = 0 only when the lattice preserves the mirror symmetry at δ = 0, 0.5 and 1, as expected."
  ]
}